reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Unleash Peak Gaming Performance with Intel Core i7-13700KF!
reviews.reviewText: The Intel Core i7-13700KF Gaming Desktop Processor is a powerhouse that delivers exceptional performance for gaming enthusiasts and content creators alike. With 16 cores (8 P-cores + 8 E-cores) and the ability to be unlocked, this processor is a game-changer in the world of desktop computing.The combination of P-cores and E-cores provides a perfect balance between high-speed single-threaded performance and efficient multi-threaded capabilities. Whether you're conquering the latest AAA titles or engaging in content creation tasks, the i7-13700KF handles it with ease.The unlocked nature of this processor caters to overclocking enthusiasts, allowing for fine-tuning to extract every ounce of performance. This feature is complemented by Intel's advanced cooling technologies, ensuring stable temperatures even under heavy workloads.Gaming experiences are taken to new heights with the i7-13700KF, thanks to its high clock speeds and robust architecture. The processor effortlessly handles demanding games and applications, providing a smooth and immersive user experience.Multitasking becomes a breeze with the ample core count, enabling seamless execution of multiple applications simultaneously. Whether you're streaming, video editing, or running virtual machines, the i7-13700KF excels in handling resource-intensive tasks.The Intel Core i7-13700KF also supports the latest DDR5 memory technology, enhancing overall system responsiveness and data transfer speeds.In conclusion, the Intel Core i7-13700KF Gaming Desktop Processor is a stellar choice for users who demand uncompromising performance. Whether you're a gamer seeking high frame rates or a content creator requiring processing power, this unlocked processor is a worthy investment that brings your desktop experience to a whole new level.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fast! Worth the price
reviews.reviewText: The Intel Core i7-13700KF presents a compelling value proposition for its price. As part of Intel's 13th Gen "Raptor Lake" series, it boasts a robust 8 Performance-core (P-core) and 8 Efficient-core (E-core) configuration, mirroring the previous-gen flagship i9-12900K but at a more accessible price point​​. This configuration, coupled with updates like larger L2 caches for P-cores and improved cache hardware-prefetchers, contributes to its outstanding performance.In terms of raw performance, the i7-13700KF demonstrates commendable prowess. It outperforms the 12th gen flagship Core i9-12900K in single and multi-core tests, albeit marginally, and shows significant performance gains over its direct predecessor, the Core i7-12700K, with a 12% and 32.5% lead in single-core and multi-core tests, respectively​​. When compared to competitors like the AMD Ryzen 7 5800X and Ryzen 9 5950X, the i7-13700KF shows a remarkable 23% and 25% single-core performance bump, and an even more impressive 67% and 15% lead in multi-core performance against these AMD chips​​.However, buyers should be aware that the Core i7-13700KF does not come with integrated graphics. For users who require onboard video capabilities, the slightly higher-priced Core i7-13700K would be the best choice. The absence of integrated graphics in the 13700KF model can be a significant consideration for those who don't plan to use a dedicated graphics card.The i7-13700KF stands out as an excellent choice for its price, offering high-end performance that rivals even some flagship models from the previous generation. Its value is particularly notable when considering its performance metrics against direct competitors and predecessors

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best processor.
reviews.reviewText: Intel is killing the competition. If you want an insanely fast PC, make this the heart of it. Or if you’re really feeling it go for an i9. I would recommend staying within the 13th generation as there’s not much about the 14th gen that makes it worth it. Out of the box this CPU will comfortably run at 5.4ghz, it performs amazing under load and in my system stays perfectly cool.This year-old CPU, blows away brand new CPU’s from the likes of Apple and AMD, I truly cannot recommend the 13th gen lineup enough, this being the centerpiece of it all.If you do get an LGA 1700 CPU, go ahead and get the bracket upgrade for your MOBO, it’ll save you time down the long run and helps to keep temps in check.
